{"cards":[{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Thermodynamics "},{"type":"headline","text":"Heat, work and energy are key concepts"},{"type":"headline","text":"Used to explain engines"},{"type":"bullet","text":"Engines involve thermal energy and work"}]},{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Thermal energy includes"},{"type":"headline","text":"Potential energy due to position"}]}],"definitions":[],"secText":["  <b>Essential Question: <\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>How can we define and quantify the thermal energy and temperature of an object?","  <b>Enduring Understandings:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>Thermodynamics<\/a> is the study of heat, work, and energy.<br \/>2. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>Thermal energy<\/a> is the energy due to the molecular potential and kinetic energy within an object. Thermal energy is measured in <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='1'>joules<\/a>.<br \/>3. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>Temperature<\/a> is the measure of the kinetic energy of the molecules within an object. Temperature can be measured with <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='1'>thermometers<\/a>.","  <b>Vocabulary:<\/b>  <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>thermodynamics<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>macroscopic<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>microscopic<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>thermal (internal) energy<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>temperature<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='11' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='1'>thermometer<\/a>","  <b>STEM Skills:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='6' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>work<\/a>.<br \/>2. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='6' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>kinetic energy<\/a>."],"objNames":["wb_thermodynamics_concept1","wb_thermal_energy_concepta"]}